Minister Godongwana briefs media ahead of US bilateral talks JOHANNESBURG - Finance Minister Enoch Godongwana says the United States ranks among South Africa’s top trading partners. He was addressing a media briefing along with US Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen. Godongwana says he’s hoping the partnership will continue, as it serves as a critical launchpad for the development of both economies. Yellen says her country is proud to have committed itself as a partner to South Africa’s Just Energy Transition. She says the partnership represents South Africa’s bold first step toward expanding electricity access and reliability. Watch the full briefing in the video above